sourceQuestion:
If L is a regular language over Sigma = {a, b}, which one of the following languages is NOT regular?
A. L^R = {xy | x in L, y^R in L}
B. {ww^R | w in L}
C. Prefix(L) = {x in Sigma* | there exists y in Sigma* such that xy in L}
D. Suffix(L) = {y in Sigma* | there exists x in Sigma* such that xy in L}

Let L be an arbitrary regular language accepted by a minimal DFA with k states. Which one of the following languages must necessarily be accepted by a minimal DFA with k states?
A. L - {0}
B. L . {0}
C. (0,1)* - L
D. L . L

