sourceQuestion:
Let Sigma = {a, b, c}. For z in Sigma*, and alpha in Sigma, let #_alpha(z) denote the number of occurrences of alpha in z. Which one or more of the following option(s) define(s) regular language(s)?

A. {a^m b^n c^p | m, n >= 0}
B. {a^(m+n) b^n c^p | m, n >= 0}
C. {w in Sigma* | #_a(w) = 3 * #_b(w), and #_c(w) = 0}
D. {w in Sigma* | #_a(w) mod 3 = #_b(w) mod 7}

Let L be a regular language. Consider the constructions on L below:
I.   repeat(L) = {ww | w in L}
II.  prefix(L) = {u | uw in L for some w in Sigma*}
III. suffix(L) = {v | uv in L for some u in Sigma*}
IV.  half(L) = {u | uw in L, |u| = |w|}

Which of the constructions could lead to a non-regular language?
A. Both I and IV
B. Only I
C. Only IV
D. Both II and III

